cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.MM, cs.DC, cs.SY

This paper deals with congestion control algorithms and their impact on fairness in network traffic. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the potential for custom parametrizations of congestion control algorithms, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) or cs.SY (Systems and Control). Additionally, the study involves analyzing traffic generated by content providers, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia) or cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
